 <Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">
Vector-Image Utility Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>
Our Vector-Image icon set includes a collection of the most commonly used icons in the healthcare, finance, and software industries. These resolution-independent XAML images can be used royalty-free in your WPF applications.  Create truly scalable, vector user interfaces.  These images can also be used in required file formats using the Save Image option.
 </Paragraph>

  <Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center"><Image Source="Images\Image.png" Stretch="None"/></Paragraph>

<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}">
 Features
</TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>

<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>There are vector images in various category-based groups within the gallery.</Paragraph></ListItem> 
<ListItem><Paragraph>Each group consists of an extensive list of industry-specific icons.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Images can be exported as XAML or any other image format.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Vector Images can be applied in any image size without loss of clarity.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Flexible image sizes and formats make this utility a UI development essential.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>


<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}">
Interactive Features
</TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>

<List>

<ListItem><Paragraph>Corresponding Vector Images are displayed in the gallery based on a selected category.</Paragraph></ListItem> 
<ListItem><Paragraph>Select an image from the gallery for it to be displayed in the Image View.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>A selected image can be exported to XAML by clicking XAML.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>A selected image can be exported to any desired image format by clicking Save Image.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Images can be resized as required.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>


</FlowDocument>
